INSERT INTO `wpag_postmeta` VALUES('887', '38', 'section_4_content', 'Gone are the days of <strong>“roll your own”</strong> stream processing.\r\n\r\nAs companies grow and they create many data repositories each different with separate operational complexities.  This data is often located in disparate silos and sometimes inaccurate, incomplete or duplicated. By conceptualizing a data architecture using AgilData Orchestration:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">• <strong>AgilData extends companies leverage of existing tools</strong>, such as SQL, to orchestrate complex big data processing systems by creating a \"view\" of the data flow for your customers, employees, products or accounts.\r\n• <strong>Dynamic Data Flows</strong> derive a more accurate picture for a data driven business with improved agility to exploit perishable insights faster for urgent business situations that require acting on in a moments notice.\r\n• Detecting these insights and <strong>acting on them against high velocity streams</strong> of incoming data will be the key to achieving and sustaining a competitive edge.</p>\r\nTo get there firms must transform their data architectures and their development teams to be agile, flexible and incrementally scalable.  An Agile Big Data Infrastructure must be <strong>Simple</strong>, <strong>Scalable</strong>, <strong>Streaming</strong> and most importantly, must be <strong>SQL</strong>.  <a href=\"http://www.agildata.com/what-is-agildata/\">Learn more here</a>.');
